Package: gainr
Type: Package
Title: Flexible Gain Charts
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Oystein Sorensen
Maintainer: Oystein Sorensen <oystein.sorensen.1985@gmail.com>
Description: Produces gain charts, which are useful tools for evaluating the performance of prediction models, particularly within customer analytics. 'gainr' extends the 'gains' package by returning a tibble, which can be used downstream for plotting and analysis.
Imports: gains (>= 1.2), dplyr (>= 0.7.4)
Suggests: ggplot2 (>= 2.2.1),
    caret (>= 6.0-79),
    glmnet (>= 2.0-16),
    glmnetUtils (>= 1.1),
    broom (>= 0.4.4),
    tibble (>= 1.4.2),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
